Alarian
Once a powerful sorcerer, little is now known of Alarian. Legend states
that he was the spark that brought the inhabitants of Geshtai out of their
barbaric existence and into the thriving modern era. Other whispers say he
forced the gods into existence with his own magic. A consistent legend is
that he grew bored with his creations, and sought to do more. Fascinated
with the lives of mortals, he eventually faced his most difficult
challenge: mastering the mysteries behind the "spark of life" that the
inhabitants of DarkWind possessed. He could create life, but it was of a
different caliber. He soon learned to shift and mold existing lifeforces
instead of creating his own. This type of sorcery soon came to be called
Necromancy. Alarian's fate is as hidden as his life. Though early
DarkWinders built crypts for his "corpse," the graves never stayed
occupied for long.
